1
00:00:11,720 --> 00:00:13,720
Previously

2
00:00:17,104 --> 00:00:20,412
That was what he said.
"My brother shot me."

3
00:00:20,776 --> 00:00:22,528
Look on the back.

4
00:00:22,804 --> 00:00:25,476
Killbrothers.

5
00:00:25,552 --> 00:00:28,692
- Morten didn't have any brothers.
- He had Killbrothers.

6
00:00:29,008 --> 00:00:33,324
- I will pay it back.
- Take that gun and shoot!

7
00:00:35,632 --> 00:00:38,940
- Are you ready?
- Just go. I'll be there in an hour.

8
00:00:44,320 --> 00:00:46,000
It's Hans!

9
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:48,088
He has a pulse.

10
00:00:48,588 --> 00:00:51,612
He's lost a hand, and
he's in a coma.

11
00:00:53,584 --> 00:00:58,264
Dad died this morning.
Now it's only you and me, Saga.

12
00:01:02,272 --> 00:01:05,580
Henrik, I thought that you wanted
to ask your new partner for help.

13
00:01:08,200 --> 00:01:12,068
- Saga, I've found something.
- We've found something on Lise's vlog.

14
00:01:12,568 --> 00:01:15,160
A Rikard Johnsson,
Ringstedgade 21 in Copenhagen.

15
00:01:15,660 --> 00:01:18,904
I'm taking over the kindergarten
that Helle started.

16
00:01:20,272 --> 00:01:23,724
Drive to Natalie Anker's.
She's the next victim.

17
00:01:24,664 --> 00:01:27,256
Drop the knife!
Stop!

18
00:01:36,668 --> 00:01:39,168
EPISODE 4

19
00:01:44,416 --> 00:01:46,528
Are you in pain, Dad?

20
00:01:48,568 --> 00:01:51,020
You can't get any more
pain killers now.

21
00:02:00,256 --> 00:02:04,220
I know that you're where
you never wanted to end up.

22
00:02:06,856 --> 00:02:10,100
It's unfair, but you
won't lie here any longer.

23
00:02:28,628 --> 00:02:30,164
Goodbye, Dad.

24
00:04:05,388 --> 00:04:09,948
The Bridge

25
00:04:13,768 --> 00:04:16,724
We're looking for 'Knightrider',
Rikard Johnsson.

26
00:04:17,724 --> 00:04:21,764
A Swede living in Copenhagen.
We're monitoring his apartment -

27
00:04:22,264 --> 00:04:24,968
- but he's hardly ever there.
Yes?

28
00:04:25,792 --> 00:04:30,640
Grew up with his mother in Helsingborg.
Moved at age 17, when she died.

29
00:04:31,140 --> 00:04:32,676
Works as a cleaner.

30
00:04:33,184 --> 00:04:37,796
His employer says
that he's a loner.

31
00:04:38,296 --> 00:04:41,016
The police in Denmark have
said exactly the same thing.

32
00:04:41,368 --> 00:04:43,768
He is wanted.
His passport has been revoked.

33
00:04:44,768 --> 00:04:47,728
- Has he left the country?
- No. He lives in isolation.

34
00:04:48,228 --> 00:04:50,968
He'll go where he feels safe.

35
00:04:51,468 --> 00:04:53,564
- Do we know where he cleaned?
- Not yet.

36
00:04:54,236 --> 00:04:56,828
- His phone?
- The call lists are on the way.

37
00:05:02,256 --> 00:05:06,136
What about Lise? It seems
like Rikard adores her.

38
00:05:06,636 --> 00:05:12,448
He thinks they have a connection.
Maybe he'll go visit her.

39
00:05:23,776 --> 00:05:27,372
- Did he say anything else?
- No, time and place. Here and now.

40
00:05:28,168 --> 00:05:29,920
What the fuck is
he looking for, man?

41
00:05:38,824 --> 00:05:43,284
- On time for once, eh?
- What are we going to do?

42
00:05:43,504 --> 00:05:46,020
You'll go to Sweden
and pick up a bag.

43
00:05:46,212 --> 00:05:49,812
- Which of you is going?
- What do you mean which one?

44
00:05:50,244 --> 00:05:51,180
One gets to stay here as collateral.

45
00:05:51,492 --> 00:05:52,072
That wasn't the deal.

46
00:05:52,572 --> 00:05:55,384
You send your girlfriend
to solve your problems.

47
00:05:55,504 --> 00:05:56,748
They're our problems.

48
00:05:57,216 --> 00:05:59,388
- I'll go.
- No.

49
00:06:00,472 --> 00:06:04,864
No, you shouldn't be alone
with him. You go, I'll stay.

50
00:06:05,344 --> 00:06:06,420
Okay.

51
00:06:07,192 --> 00:06:11,436
Here's the code to the locker
and the address. Drive carefully.

52
00:06:13,336 --> 00:06:14,652
I'll hurry.

53
00:06:51,016 --> 00:06:54,832
- Hi. We've been waiting for you.
- What have I done now?

54
00:06:55,192 --> 00:06:58,620
- Mom, I need to go to the toilet.
- Then run up.

55
00:06:59,988 --> 00:07:03,444
- Do you have good news or bad?
- Most bad, unfortunately.

56
00:07:03,496 --> 00:07:07,860
I thought so.
Here. Help out a little.

57
00:07:13,912 --> 00:07:16,908
So despite my post, he
didn't attack Bente Knudsen.

58
00:07:17,104 --> 00:07:17,440
No.

59
00:07:18,520 --> 00:07:21,836
- How did you find him at the Ankers'?
- We tracked him via the comments section.

60
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:28,828
- He might want to seek you out.
- Why's that?

61
00:07:29,328 --> 00:07:30,828
He looks like this.

62
00:07:30,928 --> 00:07:32,436
If he contacts you ...

63
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:33,640
It's Rikard.

64
00:07:34,140 --> 00:07:38,280
- Do you know him?
- He cleans our house. He has keys.

65
00:07:40,860 --> 00:07:45,300
Karen? Karen, open up!

66
00:07:49,820 --> 00:07:51,612
- Karen?
- Mom?

67
00:07:53,388 --> 00:07:55,648
Karen! Karen, open up!

68
00:07:56,148 --> 00:08:00,580
- Rikard! Don't you touch her!
- You need to let us take over.

69
00:08:01,080 --> 00:08:03,676
- Don't you touch her!
- Lise.

70
00:08:14,632 --> 00:08:18,204
Rikard, my name is Henrik Sabroe.
I'm from Copenhagen Police.

71
00:08:19,812 --> 00:08:21,708
I would very much like for you
to let Karen go.

72
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:28,692
Rikard?
Just try to talk to me, Rikard.

73
00:08:30,928 --> 00:08:33,536
I want Lise, otherwise Karen dies.

74
00:08:33,904 --> 00:08:36,372
We'll make sure, but just let
Karen go so that we can talk about ...

75
00:08:37,020 --> 00:08:39,880
No, I want Lise,
otherwise Karen dies!

76
00:08:40,276 --> 00:08:42,880
Rikard, I won't talk
before you release Karen.

77
00:08:43,380 --> 00:08:47,752
There are reinforcements on the way.
Hopefully they'll be here in fifteen minutes.

78
00:08:47,920 --> 00:08:50,752
This is your fault.

79
00:08:51,252 --> 00:08:55,184
- How's that?
- He knows that I've helped you.

80
00:08:55,792 --> 00:08:58,528
I can get in and
take Karen's place.

81
00:08:58,884 --> 00:09:00,692
You mustn't do that.
You said that you could 'get in' ...

82
00:09:01,192 --> 00:09:04,284
- There's another way.
- You will let Karen go.

83
00:09:05,392 --> 00:09:06,924
No matter what you have done -

84
00:09:07,424 --> 00:09:12,084
- you were never close
to killing a child.

85
00:09:17,032 --> 00:09:20,780
You've already crossed one line.
You don't need to cross another.

86
00:09:21,280 --> 00:09:22,780
Shut up.

87
00:09:23,824 --> 00:09:28,164
Rikard, there's something that goes
to pieces inside if you do that.

88
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:34,548
It will never be the same again.
Do you understand what I'm saying to you?

89
00:09:36,064 --> 00:09:39,740
If she dies now, then she
takes something of you with her.

90
00:09:40,240 --> 00:09:40,964
Shut up.

91
00:09:46,048 --> 00:09:51,036
To lose a child ... Life is
never quite whole again.

92
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:53,340
Do you understand what I'm saying?

93
00:09:57,112 --> 00:10:00,932
I don't know if you've tried to undo
something, but a child ...

94
00:10:01,432 --> 00:10:03,764
I'll kill her!

95
00:10:07,556 --> 00:10:09,516
Where's Saga?

96
00:10:09,640 --> 00:10:12,444
-In there.
- Come on, man.

97
00:10:14,752 --> 00:10:16,572
- Karen?
- Calmly.

98
00:10:17,728 --> 00:10:19,764
You ...

99
00:10:20,780 --> 00:10:23,676
Rikard, can you hear us?

100
00:10:24,160 --> 00:10:25,704
- I've done everything for you!
- Talk to him.

101
00:10:26,776 --> 00:10:30,012
I know that! I'm sorry,
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

102
00:10:30,568 --> 00:10:32,364
Will you please be so kind
as to not harm her?

103
00:10:32,864 --> 00:10:37,740
I'll come in if you let her out.

104
00:10:38,176 --> 00:10:41,316
Let her come out,
then I'll come in.

105
00:10:43,316 --> 00:10:44,924
Shut up.

106
00:10:45,424 --> 00:10:48,156
- Rikard, can you hear us?
- Karen.

107
00:10:48,760 --> 00:10:51,296
Shut up! Everyone shut up!

108
00:10:52,644 --> 00:10:55,484
- Mom!
- Rikard, take it easy now.

109
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:58,052
Shut up ...

110
00:11:00,688 --> 00:11:02,732
Drop the knife.

111
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:04,188
Mom!

112
00:11:12,616 --> 00:11:13,452
Saga!

113
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:20,608
Alright.

114
00:11:21,108 --> 00:11:23,652
Saga, it's fine. Come.

115
00:11:24,184 --> 00:11:28,572
It's totally fine. Come here. Drop it.
Like that. Yeah, just like that.

116
00:11:29,056 --> 00:11:37,620
It's really fine. Come on. Release it.
Here. It's fine. Like that.

117
00:11:38,944 --> 00:11:39,852
It's fine.

118
00:12:16,144 --> 00:12:17,820
Come in.

119
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:21,708
- It's time.
- Okay. I'm coming.

120
00:12:30,360 --> 00:12:34,964
I know that you're sitting and waiting
for wine and hors d'oeuvres in the foyer -

121
00:12:35,464 --> 00:12:38,148
- but you must wait
a couple minutes more.

122
00:12:38,648 --> 00:12:41,172
What have you learned today?

123
00:12:41,672 --> 00:12:47,916
Now that you've changed his tune,
you need to show the man home.

124
00:12:48,416 --> 00:12:51,524
And the boss and Agneta,
who is such an energy waster.

125
00:12:52,524 --> 00:12:55,772
Is that what you've learned?
Is what what you've learned here today?

126
00:12:57,448 --> 00:13:01,768
No, I hope that my
life story has shown -

127
00:13:02,268 --> 00:13:05,324
- that happiness is actually a choice.

128
00:13:06,324 --> 00:13:11,560
All that you need to do right now
starts here and now. It lives here.

129
00:13:12,060 --> 00:13:16,244
The feeling of how you see yourself.

130
00:13:19,456 --> 00:13:21,668
Thanks for listening.

131
00:13:29,608 --> 00:13:32,104
There. Thanks so much.

132
00:13:33,856 --> 00:13:36,020
- Hi, Claes.
- Hi, Annika.

133
00:13:37,020 --> 00:13:38,972
- That was really good. As always.
- Thanks.

134
00:13:40,936 --> 00:13:46,388
- What can I do for you today?
- Will you sign my photo from Örebro?

135
00:13:48,352 --> 00:13:51,952
You skipped the story
about the batteries today.

136
00:13:52,452 --> 00:13:54,600
I forgot that, actually.

137
00:13:55,600 --> 00:13:56,420
Here you go.

138
00:13:56,920 --> 00:13:59,876
- Can I take another?
- Yeah, of course.

139
00:14:02,752 --> 00:14:04,364
I'll be right with you.

140
00:14:09,452 --> 00:14:10,748
Okay. Thanks.

141
00:14:11,748 --> 00:14:13,288
Hi.

142
00:14:13,788 --> 00:14:16,100
- What's your name?
- Rafaela.

143
00:15:22,936 --> 00:15:23,916
No!

144
00:15:24,736 --> 00:15:28,836
Hey! What are you doing?
Give me that! Hey!

145
00:15:29,512 --> 00:15:34,524
What are you doing?
What's happening? Hey!

146
00:15:45,256 --> 00:15:46,308
Linn.

147
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:49,936
- Have you found him?
- Yes.

148
00:15:50,464 --> 00:15:53,920
- Is he here?
- He'll be here any minute.

149
00:15:54,256 --> 00:15:55,908
I want to be part
of the interrogation.

150
00:15:57,760 --> 00:15:59,728
That's not an option.

151
00:16:00,228 --> 00:16:03,544
You may be allowed to observe,
but you cannot take an active part.

152
00:16:03,904 --> 00:16:06,928
- Okay.
- Excuse me.

153
00:16:12,664 --> 00:16:14,700
Why did you go in?

154
00:16:17,872 --> 00:16:21,692
If the hostage is in imminent danger,
the police officer must ...

155
00:16:22,192 --> 00:16:26,436
Yeah, I know the rules, but
that wasn't what I meant.

156
00:16:26,936 --> 00:16:30,260
- That was what you asked about.
- Okay.

157
00:16:31,260 --> 00:16:33,800
So I'll ask like this.

158
00:16:36,592 --> 00:16:38,944
How has your father's
death affected you?

159
00:16:39,444 --> 00:16:42,328
As I said, we weren't close.

160
00:16:42,828 --> 00:16:47,632
- And that Hans is still in a coma?
- That doesn't affect my work.

161
00:16:48,132 --> 00:16:51,380
So that's not why you've
been a little reckless?

162
00:16:51,880 --> 00:16:57,768
I'm not reckless. I probably saved Karen
and Natalie Anker. It's just my job.

163
00:17:00,232 --> 00:17:02,412
Your mom called.

164
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:06,472
- Why?
- She's worried about you.

165
00:17:06,972 --> 00:17:09,496
You have not processed
what's happened.

166
00:17:09,996 --> 00:17:12,524
She has no right to
talk to you about me.

167
00:17:13,524 --> 00:17:16,192
She would you like you
to come to the memorial service.

168
00:17:17,488 --> 00:17:19,000
Rikard has been treated.
He's here now.

169
00:17:19,500 --> 00:17:23,748
- And his defender too?
- He doesn't want one.

170
00:17:26,348 --> 00:17:31,960
Helle Anker. Fabian Christensen.
Hans Pettersson.

171
00:17:39,160 --> 00:17:40,428
Tell us about them.

172
00:17:43,216 --> 00:17:44,340
Come on.

173
00:17:47,056 --> 00:17:51,440
A lawyer would say that it's
always best to talk with us.

174
00:17:58,888 --> 00:18:02,144
We're not going to let you go
just because you don't confess.

175
00:18:04,332 --> 00:18:06,540
I really thought you were
proud of what you've done.

176
00:18:07,960 --> 00:18:11,964
Lise may not have appreciated it,
but you have made a difference.

177
00:18:13,384 --> 00:18:17,532
You've surely done something good,
haven't you? You made a real difference.

178
00:18:20,008 --> 00:18:22,236
Just look at these photos.

179
00:18:23,440 --> 00:18:27,804
Helle Anker. Fabian Christensen.

180
00:18:30,928 --> 00:18:32,916
Hans Pettersson.

181
00:18:35,848 --> 00:18:37,260
Shall we start with Hans?

182
00:19:21,760 --> 00:19:23,724
Had they planned to smuggle
it across the bridge?

183
00:19:24,140 --> 00:19:25,668
Yeah.

184
00:19:28,048 --> 00:19:31,092
- Do we know what's in it?
- No.

185
00:19:31,696 --> 00:19:34,476
- Shall we open it?
- I don't need to know that.

186
00:19:35,008 --> 00:19:38,100
Marc owes money
to Lukas Stenstrup.

187
00:19:38,560 --> 00:19:41,244
I think it's payment for
some of the debt.

188
00:19:41,652 --> 00:19:45,612
I don't want to know. Colbert,
just make sure it's resolved.

189
00:19:46,312 --> 00:19:47,916
I will, Freddie.

190
00:19:59,680 --> 00:20:02,628
What was it you said
to Lise in the apartment?

191
00:20:08,584 --> 00:20:09,900
"You failed me."

192
00:20:13,816 --> 00:20:15,060
That hurts.

193
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:20,172
Then you get angry.

194
00:20:23,296 --> 00:20:24,900
Was that what happened?

195
00:20:29,820 --> 00:20:30,804
Come on.

196
00:20:45,972 --> 00:20:48,468
Linn. They must get him to talk.

197
00:20:49,552 --> 00:20:52,372
- Is he saying anything?
- Not a word.

198
00:20:52,872 --> 00:20:55,408
He will. We have time.

199
00:20:55,908 --> 00:20:59,196
It's not enough. We must connect
him to the murders, to Hans.

200
00:21:00,232 --> 00:21:01,912
Come with me.

201
00:21:04,576 --> 00:21:08,964
It must be very difficult for you.
We're investigating several murders -

202
00:21:09,464 --> 00:21:13,356
- and a brutal attack on a
police chief, not your husband.

203
00:21:13,840 --> 00:21:18,448
You must take a step back.
You cannot come and go as you wish.

204
00:21:18,880 --> 00:21:22,820
- I have employees here.
- Lent to my department, under my command.

205
00:21:25,264 --> 00:21:28,860
I wanted to be accommodating
because I feel for you -

206
00:21:29,360 --> 00:21:31,888
- but in reality that's wrong.

207
00:21:32,388 --> 00:21:34,916
You're personally involved.
You're not thinking clearly.

208
00:21:35,416 --> 00:21:36,876
You don't know what I'm thinking!

209
00:21:48,420 --> 00:21:50,588
- Do you have it good here?
- In this division?

210
00:21:51,448 --> 00:21:54,264
- In my husband's office.
- It's only temporary.

211
00:21:54,856 --> 00:21:56,748
Yeah. It is.

212
00:22:10,504 --> 00:22:15,612
My grandfather risked everything
and started EkdahlsHus -

213
00:22:16,112 --> 00:22:19,288
- so not only my mother, but
all families were given the opportunity -

214
00:22:19,788 --> 00:22:24,684
- to buy and live in a good, solid,
nice house for a reasonable price.

215
00:22:27,208 --> 00:22:30,952
We're now opening our eleventh branch
in the North, but the first in Denmark.

216
00:22:31,452 --> 00:22:33,476
It's about time, isn't it?

217
00:22:35,800 --> 00:22:37,700
Then let's cut the ribbon.

218
00:22:42,520 --> 00:22:45,112
- Good speech.
- What are you doing here?

219
00:22:45,612 --> 00:22:48,420
Saying hi to my girlfriend.

220
00:22:48,920 --> 00:22:53,444
I've booked a table at
a restaurant tonight at 8:00.

221
00:22:54,444 --> 00:22:57,832
- Can you make it?
- I really don't know.

222
00:22:58,332 --> 00:23:02,292
- Stop it. No one knows you in Denmark.
- You never know.

223
00:23:02,632 --> 00:23:09,096
You met your best friend's son
in Copenhagen and ate dinner together.

224
00:23:10,052 --> 00:23:13,292
- Anna.
- Yeah. I'm coming.

225
00:23:14,292 --> 00:23:17,756
I'll try. I'm not promising anything,
but I will try.

226
00:23:42,660 --> 00:23:43,620
Hi.

227
00:23:44,488 --> 00:23:46,884
- How did it go?
- Not so good.

228
00:23:48,040 --> 00:23:49,788
What now? Jeanette?

229
00:23:58,288 --> 00:24:02,076
- I lost the bag.
- What?

230
00:24:02,156 --> 00:24:04,908
There were some men who drove
up beside me and just took it.

231
00:24:08,608 --> 00:24:09,756
Sit down.

232
00:24:19,744 --> 00:24:25,212
Here's 7500. It's not much, but
it's all I could get.

233
00:24:27,564 --> 00:24:29,028
You can also have the car.

234
00:24:32,176 --> 00:24:35,004
Do you have any idea
what that bag was worth?

235
00:24:35,416 --> 00:24:39,060
- Surely more than 78,000.
- Far more than 78,000.

236
00:24:59,508 --> 00:25:01,044
I promise I'll get the money.

237
00:25:05,700 --> 00:25:08,992
I'll get your money.
I'll find a solution to this shit.

238
00:25:09,492 --> 00:25:11,388
Shut the fuck up, man.

239
00:25:29,416 --> 00:25:32,460
From now on you don't owe
me shit. Do you understand?

240
00:25:34,620 --> 00:25:35,868
