00:50:18,156 --> 00:50:20,200
Welcome home.

485
00:50:20,700 --> 00:50:22,792
- How did it go in Copenhagen?
- Good, thanks.

486
00:50:23,292 --> 00:50:27,312
- Did you meet up with Ulrik and Gunilla?
- No, I was too busy.

487
00:50:29,128 --> 00:50:31,720
- Hi, Mom.
- What the hell are you doing to me?

488
00:50:32,724 --> 00:50:37,548
- I've just come home from Copenhagen.
- Are you near a computer?

489
00:50:38,048 --> 00:50:41,248
Look at Aftonposten,
then call me.

490
00:50:59,356 --> 00:51:05,396
EUROVISION STAR HAS
SECRET TRYST IN COPENHAGEN.

491
00:51:44,612 --> 00:51:46,144
What did you say her name was?

492
00:51:46,576 --> 00:51:50,724
Her name is Helle Anker.
His name is Lars Ove Abrahamsson.

493
00:51:54,784 --> 00:51:58,288
No. Sorry.

494
00:51:59,180 --> 00:52:01,516
Listen ...

495
00:52:02,704 --> 00:52:05,652
You've worked together
with Hans a long time now.

496
00:52:06,152 --> 00:52:07,624
Yes.

497
00:52:08,124 --> 00:52:12,016
Have you met his new wife?
Lillian?

498
00:52:12,516 --> 00:52:14,968
- Yes, many times.
- Karin.

499
00:52:15,496 --> 00:52:20,676
We want to know if there's a connection
between your ex-husband and these two.

500
00:52:21,156 --> 00:52:23,532
Why did the same person
want to hurt them?

501
00:52:23,800 --> 00:52:27,976
I understand, but I can't
be of help, unfortunately.

502
00:52:28,648 --> 00:52:31,172
What is she like? Lillian?

503
00:52:32,172 --> 00:52:34,280
What is she like?

504
00:52:34,780 --> 00:52:39,244
She's nice. Police Chief
in Copenhagen. Younger than you.

505
00:52:41,272 --> 00:52:44,520
It all went so fast.

506
00:52:45,020 --> 00:52:47,228
Wedding and new flat
and all of that.

507
00:52:47,944 --> 00:52:52,480
I can understand that. If you
think of anything else -

508
00:52:52,980 --> 00:52:55,380
- please call us.

509
00:53:03,856 --> 00:53:06,824
Was he different with her?

510
00:53:07,480 --> 00:53:10,932
He came late now and then. He didn't
do that when you were married.

511
00:53:13,244 --> 00:53:14,916
I understand.

512
00:53:16,644 --> 00:53:18,228
Yeah, many thanks for coming.

513
00:53:24,448 --> 00:53:27,832
Saga. Will you come with me?

514
00:53:28,332 --> 00:53:30,312
- What are we doing?
- Just come now.

515
00:54:06,952 --> 00:54:10,164
- What are we doing here?
- The memorial service is here.

516
00:54:10,984 --> 00:54:14,664
- I know that, but I don't want to be here.
- I support you.

517
00:54:15,588 --> 00:54:19,780
I think that it's
important to say goodbye.

518
00:54:20,280 --> 00:54:22,448
I can't!

519
00:54:56,272 --> 00:55:01,736
Research shows that physical contact
can hasten awakening.

520
00:55:03,832 --> 00:55:06,808
And familiar sounds such as voices.

521
00:55:07,308 --> 00:55:10,044
So I can tell you
what's happening at work.

522
00:55:10,720 --> 00:55:14,680
Linn, your replacement, wanted me
to go to my dad's memorial service -

523
00:55:15,180 --> 00:55:17,316
- but I couldn't.

524
00:55:24,760 --> 00:55:26,680
My mom ...

525
00:55:31,336 --> 00:55:33,644
My mom made my sister
sick in front of me.

526
00:55:36,016 --> 00:55:40,720
Everything pointed to Münchhausen By
Proxy. I had to get her away from there.

527
00:55:41,016 --> 00:55:43,976
Otherwise I was afraid that
she would die.

528
00:55:50,276 --> 00:55:54,232
I couldn't have done differently.

529
00:55:58,912 --> 00:56:02,992
Hans ... It would be really good
if you woke up now.

530
00:56:08,152 --> 00:56:09,260
Hans.

531
00:56:20,560 --> 00:56:22,508
Who was that with
Lukas Stenstrup?

532
00:56:23,008 --> 00:56:26,820
His name is Mehmet. It was he
who drove the car the night of the 6th.

533
00:56:27,208 --> 00:56:28,524
Did he say why?

534
00:56:29,024 --> 00:56:30,996
Yeah. He had to visit
his girlfriend in Lund -

535
00:56:31,496 --> 00:56:34,820
- but one cannot use the
car for private purposes.

536
00:56:35,820 --> 00:56:40,056
Maja Nyrén, the girlfriend, confirms
that Mehmet was there until 4:00.

537
00:56:41,056 --> 00:56:44,444
It fits with the times on the camera.
But we cannot rely on one person.

538
00:56:45,444 --> 00:56:49,192
See if Øresundsbroen has photos,
and if one can see the driver.

539
00:56:49,648 --> 00:56:51,568
Okay.

540
00:56:53,560 --> 00:56:54,372
Good work.

541
00:56:55,768 --> 00:56:58,452
- I'm not in trouble, right?
- Fuck no.

542
00:56:59,728 --> 00:57:02,964
- Who really had the car?
- Just get in.

543
00:57:51,500 --> 00:57:52,972
Reported Missing

544
